The '''Telosian Council''' was the governing body of the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Telos IV]] in the wake of the [[Jedi Civil War]]. During the leadup to the [[Telosian Restoration Project]], it was highly infiltrated by [[Czerka Arms/Legends|Czerka Corporation]] lobbyists who sought to integrate the company into the new government as much as possible in order to maximize profits. Nominally in control of security in the form of the [[Telos Security Force]], the Telosian Council was also in charge of overseeing the many [[Restoration Zone]]s on the surface that lay in the shadow of [[Citadel Station]] as well as the Station's infrastructure.

Thanks largely to the actions of the [[Meetra Surik|Jedi Exile]] in securing certain evidence and witnesses for the Council's deliberation, they were able to finally expunge Czerka and the [[Exchange]] from Citadel Station and Telos itself, though the many [[Mercenary/Legends|mercenaries]] that the corporation had hired remained a threat.

